[
  {
    "id": "grammar:tae-kim:formal-de-aru",
    "source_id": "tae-kim-grammar",
    "source_key": "tae-kim:formal-de-aru",
    "slug": "formal-de-aru",
    "category": "register",
    "list_name": "formal-reasoning",
    "expression": "～である",
    "connection": "名词／な形容词词干 + である；过去形为「であった」，否定形为「ではない」",
    "explanation_zh": "用于论文、说明文和正式陈述，以较客观、断定的语气表达判断；它属于普通体，不等于礼貌体「です／ます」。",
    "source_url": "https://guidetojapanese.org/learn/grammar/formal",
    "license_key": "cc-by-nc-sa-3.0",
    "content_version": "2026-07-15",
    "display_order": 91,
    "published": true,
    "path": "advanced",
    "examples": [
      {"ja": "この制度の目的は、地域間の格差を減らすことである。", "zh": "这项制度的目的是缩小地区之间的差距。", "source": "kotonoha-original"}
    ],
    "common_mistakes": [
      "「である」是正式的普通体，并不会自动使句子更尊敬；对客户礼貌陈述通常用「です／でございます」，不要在同一段落无目的地混用文体。"
    ],
    "related_entries": ["grammar:tae-kim:da-desu", "grammar:tae-kim:gozaru"]
  },
  {
    "id": "grammar:tae-kim:dewa-arumai",
    "source_id": "tae-kim-grammar",
    "source_key": "tae-kim:dewa-arumai",
    "slug": "dewa-arumai",
    "category": "modality",
    "list_name": "formal-reasoning",
    "expression": "～ではあるまい",
    "connection": "名词／な形容词词干 + ではあるまい；「あるまい」是「ある」的否定推量形式",
    "explanation_zh": "以正式、书面语气推测某事大概并非如此，相当于较郑重的「～ではないだろう」。",
    "source_url": "https://guidetojapanese.org/learn/grammar/volitional2",
    "license_key": "cc-by-nc-sa-3.0",
    "content_version": "2026-07-15",
    "display_order": 92,
    "published": true,
    "path": "advanced",
    "examples": [
      {"ja": "彼の沈黙は、単なる偶然ではあるまい。", "zh": "他的沉默大概不只是偶然。", "source": "kotonoha-original"}
    ],
    "common_mistakes": [
      "「ではあるまい」表示否定推量，不是直接断言「不是」；若要明确否定事实，用「ではない」，不要把两者当作只差正式程度。"
    ],
    "related_entries": ["grammar:tae-kim:formal-de-aru", "grammar:tae-kim:darou-volitional"]
  },
  {
    "id": "grammar:tae-kim:gozaru",
    "source_id": "tae-kim-grammar",
    "source_key": "tae-kim:gozaru",
    "slug": "gozaru",
    "category": "politeness",
    "list_name": "formal-reasoning",
    "expression": "ござる／ございます",
    "connection": "「ある」的郑重语为「ござる」；现代礼貌表达常用「ございます」，判断句用名词／な形容词词干 + でございます",
    "explanation_zh": "「ございます」用于服务场景或郑重陈述存在与判断；辞书形「ござる」在现代日常会话中带古风或角色化色彩。",
    "source_url": "https://guidetojapanese.org/learn/grammar/honorific",
    "license_key": "cc-by-nc-sa-3.0",
    "content_version": "2026-07-15",
    "display_order": 93,
    "published": true,
    "path": "advanced",
    "examples": [
      {"ja": "ご予約のお席はこちらでございます。", "zh": "您预约的座位在这里。", "source": "kotonoha-original"}
    ],
    "common_mistakes": [
      "现代接待语通常说「ございます／でございます」，直接句末说「でござる」会显得古风；也不要把郑重语误当成所有场合都自然的尊敬语。"
    ],
    "related_entries": ["grammar:tae-kim:formal-de-aru", "grammar:tae-kim:honorific-verbs"]
  },
  {
    "id": "grammar:tae-kim:wake-ga-nai",
    "source_id": "tae-kim-grammar",
    "source_key": "tae-kim:wake-ga-nai",
    "slug": "wake-ga-nai",
    "category": "reasoning",
    "list_name": "formal-reasoning",
    "expression": "～わけがない",
    "connection": "动词／い形容词普通形 + わけがない；名词／な形容词词干 + なわけがない",
    "explanation_zh": "根据常识、证据或前提强烈判断“绝不可能”。它否定的是结论的可能性；「わけにはいかない」则表示受责任或处境约束而不能做。",
    "source_url": "https://guidetojapanese.org/learn/grammar/reasoning",
    "license_key": "cc-by-nc-sa-3.0",
    "content_version": "2026-07-15",
    "display_order": 94,
    "published": true,
    "path": "advanced",
    "examples": [
      {"ja": "鍵は私が持っているのだから、彼が先に入れるわけがない。", "zh": "钥匙在我这里，所以他不可能先进去。", "source": "kotonoha-original"}
    ],
    "common_mistakes": [
      "「わけがない」不是“因为义务所以不能”；要表达明知能做、但因责任不能做，应使用「わけにはいかない」。"
    ],
    "related_entries": ["grammar:tae-kim:wake-explanation", "grammar:tae-kim:wake-ni-wa-ikanai"]
  },
  {
    "id": "grammar:tae-kim:wake-ni-wa-ikanai",
    "source_id": "tae-kim-grammar",
    "source_key": "tae-kim:wake-ni-wa-ikanai",
    "slug": "wake-ni-wa-ikanai",
    "category": "obligation",
    "list_name": "formal-reasoning",
    "expression": "～わけにはいかない",
    "connection": "动词辞书形 + わけにはいかない；动词ない形 + わけにはいかない表示“不能不做”，即必须做",
    "explanation_zh": "动作本身并非不可能，但因责任、立场或社会情理而不能选择去做；这与判断事情不可能成立的「わけがない」不同。",
    "source_url": "https://guidetojapanese.org/learn/grammar/reasoning",
    "license_key": "cc-by-nc-sa-3.0",
    "content_version": "2026-07-15",
    "display_order": 95,
    "published": true,
    "path": "advanced",
    "examples": [
      {"ja": "明日は私が責任者なので、休むわけにはいかない。", "zh": "明天我是负责人，所以不能请假。", "source": "kotonoha-original"}
    ],
    "common_mistakes": [
      "不要把「行かないわけにはいかない」理解成“不可能去”；双重否定表示因责任“不能不去”，也就是必须去。"
    ],
    "related_entries": ["grammar:tae-kim:wake-ga-nai", "grammar:tae-kim:te-wa-ikenai"]
  },
  {
    "id": "grammar:tae-kim:mono-da",
    "source_id": "tae-kim-grammar",
    "source_key": "tae-kim:mono-da",
    "slug": "mono-da",
    "category": "discourse",
    "list_name": "formal-reasoning",
    "expression": "～ものだ",
    "connection": "动词／い形容词普通形 + ものだ；名词／な形容词词干 + なものだ；回忆过去常用「～たものだ」",
    "explanation_zh": "可把内容概括为一般常理、感叹，或用过去形回忆从前经常发生的事；这里的「もの」已语法化，不单指具体物品。",
    "source_url": "https://www.guidetojapanese.org/blog/2014/08/20/%E6%9A%87%E3%81%A4%E3%81%B6%E3%81%97%E3%81%AE%E6%8A%95%E7%A8%BF/",
    "license_key": "cc-by-nc-sa-3.0",
    "content_version": "2026-07-15",
    "display_order": 96,
    "published": true,
    "path": "advanced",
    "examples": [
      {"ja": "子どものころは、暗くなるまで川で遊んだものだ。", "zh": "小时候常常在河边玩到天黑。", "source": "kotonoha-original"}
    ],
    "common_mistakes": [
      "回忆习惯时「～たものだ」表示过去反复发生，不宜只描述一次事件；也不要把句末语法一律按实体名词“东西”翻译。"
    ],
    "related_entries": ["grammar:tae-kim:generic-mono", "grammar:tae-kim:ta-koto-ga-aru"]
  },
  {
    "id": "grammar:tae-kim:mono-no",
    "source_id": "tae-kim-grammar",
    "source_key": "tae-kim:mono-no",
    "slug": "mono-no",
    "category": "contrast",
    "list_name": "formal-reasoning",
    "expression": "～ものの",
    "connection": "动词／い形容词普通形 + ものの；名词 + であるものの；な形容词词干 + なものの／であるものの",
    "explanation_zh": "以较书面的语气承认前项事实，再说明后项出现不相称、未达预期或相反的结果。",
    "source_url": "https://www.guidetojapanese.org/blog/2011/07/15/what-im-reading-today/",
    "license_key": "cc-by-nc-sa-3.0",
    "content_version": "2026-07-15",
    "display_order": 97,
    "published": true,
    "path": "advanced",
    "examples": [
      {"ja": "参加すると約束したものの、急な仕事で行けなくなった。", "zh": "虽然答应参加，却因为临时工作而去不了了。", "source": "kotonoha-original"}
    ],
    "common_mistakes": [
      "「ものの」是连接两个小句的转折形式，不是实体名词「もの」加所属助词「の」；后项应体现与前项预期不一致。"
    ],
    "related_entries": ["grammar:tae-kim:noni-contrast", "grammar:tae-kim:mono-da"]
  },
  {
    "id": "grammar:tae-kim:sae-minimum",
    "source_id": "tae-kim-grammar",
    "source_key": "tae-kim:sae-minimum",
    "slug": "sae-minimum",
    "category": "focus",
    "list_name": "minimum-and-signs",
    "expression": "（で）さえ",
    "connection": "名词 + さえ／でさえ；动词ます形去掉ます + さえすれば；动词て形 + さえ + 补助动词",
    "explanation_zh": "提出最低或极端项目，表示“连……都”或“只要……就”。「すら」较书面且以名词为主；「おろか」则先排除更高层项目，再强调较低层也不成立。",
    "source_url": "https://guidetojapanese.org/learn/grammar/even",
    "license_key": "cc-by-nc-sa-3.0",
    "content_version": "2026-07-15",
    "display_order": 98,
    "published": true,
    "path": "advanced",
    "examples": [
      {"ja": "申込書に名前さえ書けば、受付は完了します。", "zh": "申请表上只要写名字，受理就完成了。", "source": "kotonoha-original"}
    ],
    "common_mistakes": [
      "「さえ」不只表示负面的“连……也不”，也可配合条件表示最低充分条件；不要把它与主要限于名词、语气较书面的「すら」完全等同。"
    ],
    "related_entries": ["grammar:tae-kim:sura-minimum", "grammar:tae-kim:o-roka"]
  },
  {
    "id": "grammar:tae-kim:sura-minimum",
    "source_id": "tae-kim-grammar",
    "source_key": "tae-kim:sura-minimum",
    "slug": "sura-minimum",
    "category": "focus",
    "list_name": "minimum-and-signs",
    "expression": "（で）すら",
    "connection": "名词 + すら／ですら；附着在含助词的名词项后时保留必要的格关系",
    "explanation_zh": "以偏书面、强调的方式提出意外的最低项目，主要接名词。「さえ」适用范围更广；「おろか」采用“A姑且不论，连B也……”的两级结构。",
    "source_url": "https://guidetojapanese.org/learn/grammar/even",
    "license_key": "cc-by-nc-sa-3.0",
    "content_version": "2026-07-15",
    "display_order": 99,
    "published": true,
    "path": "advanced",
    "examples": [
      {"ja": "長年の専門家ですら、その原因を説明できなかった。", "zh": "就连多年的专家也无法解释其原因。", "source": "kotonoha-original"}
    ],
    "common_mistakes": [
      "「すら」通常直接突出名词，不像「さえ」那样常构成「动词词干＋さえすれば」；日常口语也往往优先用「さえ」。"
    ],
    "related_entries": ["grammar:tae-kim:sae-minimum", "grammar:tae-kim:o-roka"]
  },
  {
    "id": "grammar:tae-kim:o-roka",
    "source_id": "tae-kim-grammar",
    "source_key": "tae-kim:o-roka",
    "slug": "o-roka",
    "category": "focus",
    "list_name": "minimum-and-signs",
    "expression": "～はおろか",
    "connection": "名词A + はおろか、名词B + も／さえ／すら + 谓语",
    "explanation_zh": "先说较高门槛的A根本不必谈，再指出连较低门槛的B也不成立。它构造两个层级，不同于单独聚焦一个最低项的「さえ／すら」。",
    "source_url": "https://guidetojapanese.org/learn/grammar/even",
    "license_key": "cc-by-nc-sa-3.0",
    "content_version": "2026-07-15",
    "display_order": 100,
    "published": true,
    "path": "advanced",
    "examples": [
      {"ja": "海外旅行はおろか、県外にさえ出たことがない。", "zh": "别说出国旅行了，我甚至都没出过本县。", "source": "kotonoha-original"}
    ],
    "common_mistakes": [
      "A应是更高、更难达到的项目，B是更基础的项目；若把层级颠倒，句子的递进逻辑会不自然。"
    ],
    "related_entries": ["grammar:tae-kim:sae-minimum", "grammar:tae-kim:sura-minimum"]
  },
  {
    "id": "grammar:tae-kim:garu-signs",
    "source_id": "tae-kim-grammar",
    "source_key": "tae-kim:garu-signs",
    "slug": "garu-signs",
    "category": "evidentiality",
    "list_name": "minimum-and-signs",
    "expression": "～がる",
    "connection": "い形容词去掉い + がる；な形容词词干 + がる；「欲しい→欲しがる」，「～たい→～たがる」",
    "explanation_zh": "根据可观察到的表情或行为描述他人的感受、欲望；接上「がる」后整体按五段动词变化。",
    "source_url": "https://guidetojapanese.org/learn/grammar/signs",
    "license_key": "cc-by-nc-sa-3.0",
    "content_version": "2026-07-15",
    "display_order": 101,
    "published": true,
    "path": "advanced",
    "examples": [
      {"ja": "弟は注射を見ると、いつも怖がる。", "zh": "弟弟一看到打针就总是显得害怕。", "source": "kotonoha-original"}
    ],
    "common_mistakes": [
      "自己的当下感受通常直接说「怖い／うれしい」，不说「怖がる」；「～がる」表示从外在迹象观察到的表现。"
    ],
    "related_entries": ["grammar:tae-kim:tagaru-desire", "grammar:tae-kim:sou-ni-mieru"]
  },
  {
    "id": "grammar:tae-kim:sou-ni-mieru",
    "source_id": "tae-kim-grammar",
    "source_key": "tae-kim:sou-ni-mieru",
    "slug": "sou-ni-mieru",
    "category": "evidentiality",
    "list_name": "minimum-and-signs",
    "expression": "～そうに見える",
    "connection": "动词ます形去掉ます／い形容词去掉い／な形容词词干 + そうに見える；「いい→よさそう」，「ない→なさそう」",
    "explanation_zh": "根据眼前外观判断某状态似乎如此；「そう」变为副词形「そうに」来修饰「見える」。",
    "source_url": "https://guidetojapanese.org/learn/grammar/similarity",
    "license_key": "cc-by-nc-sa-3.0",
    "content_version": "2026-07-15",
    "display_order": 102,
    "published": true,
    "path": "advanced",
    "examples": [
      {"ja": "この椅子は丈夫そうに見えるが、とても軽い。", "zh": "这把椅子看起来很结实，却非常轻。", "source": "kotonoha-original"}
    ],
    "common_mistakes": [
      "外观样态的「そう」接词干，不能照搬传闻「普通形＋そうだ」；例如“看起来好”说「よさそうに見える」，不是「いいそうに見える」。"
    ],
    "related_entries": ["grammar:tae-kim:sou-appearance", "grammar:tae-kim:garu-signs"]
  },
  {
    "id": "grammar:tae-kim:kaneru",
    "source_id": "tae-kim-grammar",
    "source_key": "tae-kim:kaneru",
    "slug": "kaneru",
    "category": "modality",
    "list_name": "feasibility-and-tendency",
    "expression": "～かねる",
    "connection": "动词ます形去掉ます + かねる；礼貌场合常用「～かねます」",
    "explanation_zh": "表示说话者因立场、判断或心理阻力难以做某事，常用于正式而克制的拒绝。「かねない」不是它的普通否定，而表示负面事情可能发生。",
    "source_url": "https://guidetojapanese.org/learn/grammar/feasibility",
    "license_key": "cc-by-nc-sa-3.0",
    "content_version": "2026-07-15",
    "display_order": 103,
    "published": true,
    "path": "advanced",
    "examples": [
      {"ja": "個別の審査結果については、お答えしかねます。", "zh": "关于个别审查结果，我们不便回答。", "source": "kotonoha-original"}
    ],
    "common_mistakes": [
      "「かねる」多表达基于立场的困难或婉转拒绝，不宜替代所有身体能力上的“不会”；也不要按字面把「かねない」理解成“不能”。"
    ],
    "related_entries": ["grammar:tae-kim:kanenai", "grammar:tae-kim:potential-form"]
  },
  {
    "id": "grammar:tae-kim:kanenai",
    "source_id": "tae-kim-grammar",
    "source_key": "tae-kim:kanenai",
    "slug": "kanenai",
    "category": "modality",
    "list_name": "feasibility-and-tendency",
    "expression": "～かねない",
    "connection": "动词ます形去掉ます + かねない",
    "explanation_zh": "指出某种不希望出现的结果有发生风险，可理解为“很可能会／恐怕会”。虽然外形带「ない」，意义并不是「かねる」的简单否定。",
    "source_url": "https://guidetojapanese.org/learn/grammar/feasibility",
    "license_key": "cc-by-nc-sa-3.0",
    "content_version": "2026-07-15",
    "display_order": 104,
    "published": true,
    "path": "advanced",
    "examples": [
      {"ja": "このまま確認を省けば、重大な事故につながりかねない。", "zh": "如果继续省略检查，可能会导致重大事故。", "source": "kotonoha-original"}
    ],
    "common_mistakes": [
      "「かねない」通常提示不良后果的可能性或风险；要婉转拒绝“难以回答”应说「答えかねる」，不是「答えかねない」。"
    ],
    "related_entries": ["grammar:tae-kim:kaneru", "grammar:tae-kim:sou-appearance"]
  },
  {
    "id": "grammar:tae-kim:shikata-ga-nai",
    "source_id": "tae-kim-grammar",
    "source_key": "tae-kim:shikata-ga-nai",
    "slug": "shikata-ga-nai",
    "category": "modality",
    "list_name": "feasibility-and-tendency",
    "expression": "仕方がない／しょうがない",
    "connection": "完整句 + のは仕方がない；动词て形 + も仕方がない；也可作为固定句「仕方がない」独立使用",
    "explanation_zh": "接受某个已经无法改变或没有现实办法避免的局面；口语常说「しょうがない」。",
    "source_url": "https://guidetojapanese.org/learn/grammar/feasibility",
    "license_key": "cc-by-nc-sa-3.0",
